profile_positions.description:
Main responsibilities:
- design new functionality for application tools;
- UX-research;
- look at metrics and behavioral analytics;
- write requirements and documentation;
- prototype validation after UI and development
- participation in cross-team projects with other designers of the company.

I started working as a UX/UI Designer.

Worked on several products related to user support:
- external (client) - chats and bot, a bank call, "My requests".
- internal (bank employees) - workplaces for operators of contact centers, web app.

After 1.5 years, I moved to the position of Lead Product Designer on the operator's workplace platform.

Main responsibilities:
- organize the work of designers who design products for the workplace;
- describe DoR (Definition of Ready), a road map for designing a feature on our platform;
- conduct a review of the entire design that goes into production;
- created from scratch and support the design system and UI kit;
- develop a design for features inside workplaces;
- look at metrics and behavioral analytics;
- participate in the development of the workplace with teams and their Product Owners.

Results of work:

Made a complete redesign of chats on the SberBank website. After the redesign, the number of chat calls has tripled compared to the old design.

Designed a unique chat-centric page on the SberBank website:
- the growth of conversion in the registration of a loan application amounted to 9.55%;
- based on the results of the pilot, a decision was made on the further development of the project.

Within a year, with my participation from scratch in the production, the product “My requests” was launched on all platforms.

From scratch, I create the product operator's workplace together with the team:
- thanks to our work, the workplace made it possible to save up to 400 PSU (production staff unit) employees per year;
- the product has been successfully working in production for 1.5 years and more than 2,000 operators have already moved from the old CRM to a new workplace;
- set up and organized the entire design process in the product;
- instilled a love of research and CustDev'u;
- I develop the design community of the product.

I mentor and train designers and CJE (Customer Journey Expert)

Designed for iOS, Android, Web.
